First, let's find the symmetric difference A △ B. The symmetric difference between two sets A and B is the set of elements which are in either of the sets, but not in their intersection. In other words, (A △ B) = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B).

A = {1, 2, 3, 4}
B = {3, 4, 5, 6}

A ∪ B = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6} (union of A and B)
A ∩ B = {3, 4} (intersection of A and B)

Now, we can find the symmetric difference A △ B:

A △ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B) = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6} - {3, 4} = {1, 2, 5, 6}

Now we need to find the intersection of (A △ B) and {2, 5}:

(A △ B) ∩ {2, 5} = {1, 2, 5, 6} ∩ {2, 5} = {2, 5}

So, (A △ B) ∩ {2, 5} = {2, 5}.
